[{"id":"6cb32e00aeeb31d3ac8368694d99dbda","from":"Financial Navigator","from_email":"news@finnav.com","to":"Jeff Edwards","to_list":[{"name":"Jeff Edwards","email":"jeeproject@yahoo.com"}],"cc_list":[],"subject":"An Exciting Announcement","date":"2017-04-19T12:25:01.000Z","formatted_date":"Apr 19, 2017","formatted_time":"12:25 PM","body":"Ed Van Deman\n\nCEO and Co-Founder\n\nDear Clients and Colleagues,\n\nToday we are proud to announce that Financial Navigator, Inc. has been acquired by Asset Vantage, Inc., a global, next-generation, cloud-based asset management, accounting and reporting software company.\n\nFor the past 30+ years, as CEO of Financial Navigator, my constant goal has been to provide the leading financial reporting and accounting software solution to single family offices, multi-family offices, CPA firms, trust and estate managers and other customers.\n\nThis acquisition and our integration with Asset Vantage represent the next steps in helping us meet that continuous challenge.\n\nYou can  read the complete press release [http://www.finnav.com/press-release-2017-04.html].\n\nCombining Resources\n\nThe entire team at Financial Navigator is eager to be joining forces with Asset Vantage and is energized by the additional resources and extended reach that will result from this combination. The blending of our firms will allow us to expand our market presence and software capabilities not only in the United States, but also globally, in order to better serve our clients.\n\nGlobal Perspective\n\nWith years of experience in multiple countries and cultures, Asset Vantage brings a global perspective to its cloud-based technology solutions for the wealth management industry. Its software system provides a fully configurable portfolio reporting and reconciliation, data aggregation and analytics tool that is suitable for all asset classes, currencies and geographies. You can learn more at  [http://AssetVantage.com].\n\nStrengthening our Management Team\n\nMark Rogozinski is CEO of Asset Vantage. Based in Stamford, CT, he oversees the operations of the company in North America, Asia and the Middle East and has played a critical role in achieving the combination of our two firms. With a long history of providing financial management services to the high-net-worth market, Mark has a deep understanding of our clientele and their data reporting needs. His strategic vision, coupled with tremendous experience in our industry and a passion for customer support will prove invaluable to our future success. I look forward to working with him for many years to come.\n\nAnswering Your Questions\n\nThis event marks a major advancement in the abilities and scope of our company. Understandably, you may have questions about how this change might impact you and the Financial Navigator products and services you are currently using. For answers to such questions, please visit  FAQ about the Asset Vantage acquisition [http://www.finnav.com/faq-financial-navigator-asset-vantage.html].\n\nLooking Ahead\n\nToday, as was the case when we started many years ago, we are dedicated to providing a world-class financial reporting and accounting software solution for all our clients around the globe. With our newly expanded capabilities we are now more enthused than ever about our ability to meet and exceed your expectations.\n\nEd Van Deman\n\nCEO and Co-Founder\n\nFinancial Navigator\n\nEditor\u2019s Note: We are always interested in your comments and feedback. You can write to us at:  [editor@finnav.com].\n\nFinancial Navigator\n\n275 Saratoga Ave., Suite 260\n\nSanta Clara, CA 95050 USA\n\ninfo@finnav.com\n\n+1 800\u00ad 468-3636\n\nYou are receiving this email because you expressed interest in Financial Navigator, Inc. You can opt out anytime.                Preferences http://financialnavigator.updatemyprofile.com/r-yujkhhky-159D35F8-dldrhujlo-t  |   Unsubscribe http://em.finnav.com/t/r-u-yujkhhky-dldrhujlo-i/\n","body_html":"<!DOCTYPE html PUBL